spanGrp.span: Me, I will tell a story
Me, when I was going to dance
anin qay aa gahis hed aa gidaw dumd
ànín qày àà gàhís héd àà gídàw dúmd
Our dance, it was done in the afternoon
dumd qahany gesarmanaj gwand da sisarmanaj askwar
dúmd qàhàny gésàrmànàj gwànd dà sísàrmànàj àskwàr
ngoma ya kwetu inachezwa kuna inayochezwa mchana
There is a dance that is danced at night, and in the afternoon, you go to dance your dance
gwand da sisarmanaj musanumed askwar gu dumdang'w
'gwànd dà sìsármànàj músànúméd àskwàr gú dúmdàng''w'
kuna inayochezwa usiku mchana unaenda kucheza ngoma yako
And you wear your animal skin
If you arrive you bring your special bell for the dance
ukifika unafunga kengele maalum kwa ajili ya ngoma
You choose someone to dance with
You choose the person to dance with and you are given your song and you dance with him when...
ging'esh am wa gwahit gijegony dumdang'w aa gisarmamn aa qaremaned aowasch ad
'gíng''ésh àm wà gwáhít gíjégòny dúmdàng''w àà gísàrmàmn àà qàrémànéd aòwàsch àd'
unamchagua wa kucheza naye na unapewa wimbo wako na unacheza naye ukiwa .....
You choose the person to dance with and you start again
unamchagua wa kucheza naye unaanza tena
You choose the person to dance with here when you have worn your animal skin
ee ging'eshi aa biji gukwal aqodang'w
unamchagua wa kucheza naye huku ukiwa umevaa ngozi yako
You choose the person to dance with and you are given your song and you dance the two of you, with that person you chose
ging'eshi aa gegony dumdang'e aa gisarman qowasch iyeny aa qaremaned ng'ead
'gìng''éshí àà gégòny dúmdàng''e àà gísàrmàn qówàsch íyény àà qàrémànéd ng''éd'
unamchagua wa kucheza naye na unapewa wimbo wako ba mnacheza ngoma mkiwa wawili na yule uliye mchagua
You dance and the sun begins to shine
There is a special dance called Shandala
For the Shandala type of dance, you don't wear the animal skins, just a kanga
shandal amigad akwal aqod gikwal kangajeg
shàndàl àmígàd àkwàl àqòd gíkwàl kàngàjég
ngoma aina ya shandal huvai tena ngozi unavaa tu kanga na kucheza
And on your neck there is the metal jewelry called daroida
na shingoni mwako kuna chuma ya kusukwa inayoitwa daroida
And beads together with the special metal, for the arms you wear the clothes called kirubega
a ushanga pamoja na chuma cha kusuka maalum kwa mikononi na unavaa nguo mvao wa kirubega
We go and dance the Shandala, and often it is danced by wearing the bell which is called gurayeek
geway aa gijesarman shandaliis handal handal gesarmanid gurayek
géwày àà gíjésàrmàn shàndàlíís hàndàl hàndàl gésàrmàníd gúràyék
tunaenda na kucheza ngoma aina ya shandali shandal huwa inachezwa kwa kuvaa kengele inayoitwa gurayék
It is danced by using the gurayeek, the sun is shining and then you have to go to the youth meeting, we have a meeting, and in the morning the roosters
gesarmanid gurayek gamugd asechand agwand bat gurgwaged geang'ech aa geaway gurgwaged qaremang gwadeb eruwach aa geanyaraj ng'qaqajeg
'gésàrmàníd gúràyék gàmúgd àséchànd àgwànd bàt gúrgwàgéd géang''éch àà géawày gúrgwàgéd qàrémàng gwàdéb érúwàch àà geànyàràj ng''qàqàjég'
inachezwa kwa kutumia gurayek jua linazama na kuna kwendakikao cha vijana tunafanya kikao karibia na asubuhi majogoo
We wake and start to scatter
And we return again to the dance
And we start just like yesterday
anang'w gi ng'eshat gid het migad
You start, there is the Shandala dance, there is Gerona, there is Mulbadaw, and there is going to the meeting and then going home
ging'esh gwand shandal aa gwand geron aa gwand mulbadaw aa gwand bat girgwaged aa gwand bat quwar
'gíng''ésh gwànd shàndàl àà gwànd géròn àà gwànd múlbàdàw àà gwànd bàt gírgwàgéd àà gwànd bàt qúwàr'
unaanza kuna ngoma aina ya shandal kuna geron kuna mulbadaw na kuna kwenda kikao na kuna kwenda nyumbani
All of this will be done, it can't be postponed
su gijesin sen mandan daja gwashiny ar aqalele
sú gìjésìn sén màndàn dàjà gwáshíny àr aqàlélé
hiyo itafanyika yote hakuna itakayo hairishwa hata moja
In the old days the land we lived in was nice
qay qay darotany qay sindi darort qay amiyi
qày qày dàròtàny qày síndì dàròrt qày àmíyí
zamani nchi tuliyopo zamani ilikuwa ni nzuri
There are no youth meetings for the girls or the women
madgwand ar gil matayinyaj girgwaged qaremang aa gwand da gademga aa madgwand da ajnodig
màdgwànd ár gìl màtàyínyàj gírgwàgéd qàrémàng àà gwànd da gàdémgà àà màdgwànd dà àjnódìg
hakuna vikao vya vijana akina mama na akina mama wakubwa
Even for the men, I haven't heard of it
So, in the old days this is what it was like
